# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  .dockerignore — controls what gets sent to the Docker daemon as build
#  context. Keep this LEAN: every excluded folder = fewer bytes copied,
#  faster `docker build`, no chance of stale build artifacts getting baked
#  into a layer.
#
#  Mirror the .gitignore where it makes sense; add Docker-specific bits.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# .NET build outputs — must NEVER be sent to the daemon; they break
# multi-arch builds and bake host-specific binaries into the image.
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/TestResults/
**/coverage/

# Node — sending node_modules can be 200+ MB of pure waste.
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.next/

# Git / IDE / OS noise
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.user
*.suo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Docker artifacts themselves
docker/
.dockerignore
Dockerfile*

# Docs and ADRs aren't part of the runtime image
docs/
README.md
LICENSE
*.md

# Secrets — defensive (none should be checked in, but if a local
# .env exists we never want it landing in an image layer).
.env
.env.local
**/secrets.json
**/appsettings.*.Production.json

# User-secrets manifest (the secrets themselves live outside the repo)
**/UserSecretsId
